To open a URL in the default browser when an `ImageView` is clicked in Android, you can set an `OnClickListener` to the `ImageView` either in the XML with the `android:onClick` attribute pointing to a method in your activity, or programmatically within your activity code.

1. In your XML file, you can add an `android:onClick` attribute to the `ImageView`:

```xml
<ImageView
    android:id="@+id/firebase_logo_image"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="56dp"
    android:src="@drawable/built_with_firebase_logo_dark"
    android:scaleType="centerInside"
    android:adjustViewBounds="true"
    android:padding="6dp"
    android:clickable="true"
    android:focusable="true"
    android:onClick="openFirebaseWebsite"  <!-- Method name in the activity -->
/>
```

2. In your `Activity` that contains the `NavigationView`, define the method `openFirebaseWebsite(View view)` that will be called when the `ImageView` is clicked:

```java
public void openFirebaseWebsite(View view) {
    String url = "https://firebase.google.com/";
    Intent intent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW);
    intent.setData(Uri.parse(url));
    startActivity(intent);
}
```

Make sure that this method is public, has a return type of void, and has a `View` parameter. When the `ImageView` is clicked, this method will be called, and it will launch the default web browser to display the Firebase website.

Alternatively, if you prefer to set the click event programmatically, you can do so in your activity's `onCreate` method by finding the `ImageView` by ID and setting an `OnClickListener`:

```java
@Override
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
    setContentView(R.layout.your_layout);

    ImageView firebaseLogoImage = findViewById(R.id.firebase_logo_image);
    firebaseLogoImage.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
        @Override
        public void onClick(View v) {
            // Same Intent code as the openFirebaseWebsite method
            String url = "https://firebase.google.com/";
            Intent intent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW);
            intent.setData(Uri.parse(url));
            startActivity(intent);
        }
    });
}
```

Both methods achieve the same outcome. Choose whichever approach fits your coding style and project structure best.
